const intro = [
  "Australian homes are famously bad at holding heat, and running ducted heating or a reverse-cycle system to warm one room you're sitting in is an expensive way to stay comfortable. A good portable heater fixes that — you heat the room you're in, when you're in it, and leave the rest of the house alone.",
  "The catch is that the category is full of noise. Every heater claims to be efficient, silent and powerful. So we compared what's actually checkable: verified customer ratings and review volume from Australian buyers, heat output and coverage, safety features like tilt and overheat protection, noise, and value for money.",
  "One honest thing worth knowing before you spend: <strong>every electric resistance heater converts essentially all the electricity it draws into heat.</strong> A 1500 W heater from one brand does not produce meaningfully more warmth than a 1500 W heater from another. Real savings come from heating a smaller space for less time — not from a proprietary technology. Be sceptical of any heater sold on the promise of slashing your power bill.",
  "With that in mind, here are the portable heaters worth buying in Australia this winter, ranked by our <a href='/how-we-rate/'>Insider Score</a>.",
];

const deepDive = {
  heading: "Why the Clima Mini Heater Is Our #1 Pick",
  body: [
    "The Clima earns the top spot on flexibility rather than raw power. It plugs directly into a wall outlet with no installation, no assembly and no tools, and it's small enough to unplug and carry to another room in seconds. If your actual problem is 'the room I'm sitting in is cold' — a home office in the morning, a bedroom at night, a nursery — that's the problem it's built for, and it covers up to about 200 square feet.",
    "The safety and support side is what separates it from the cheap plug-in heaters that flood this category. It's UL safety certified with built-in overheat protection and runs quietly enough to leave on in a bedroom. It's backed by a 30-day money-back guarantee, a free replacement warranty and a 1-year manufacturer warranty — the strongest buyer protection of anything in this guide.",
    "We'll be straight about the trade-offs, because they matter. It's sold direct online rather than through Australian retailers, which means there's no independent retailer review aggregate to cross-check the manufacturer's own numbers against — so we've scored it on its verifiable specifications, safety certification, and guarantee rather than on a customer-rating average. If you specifically want the option with the strongest independent review evidence behind it, our #2 pick, the Dreo Atom 316, holds a 4.6-star average from 679 verified buyers and is an excellent choice.",
  ],
};

const highlights = [
  {
    title: "Easy Setup",
    text: "Plug it into any wall socket, set the temperature, and it's running. No installation, no tools, no assembly.",
  },
  {
    title: "Genuinely Portable",
    text: "Light and compact enough to unplug and carry to whichever room you're actually using.",
